<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-17T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-17T01:00:00-05:00" n="625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War, 1939/394:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-17T09:00:00+03:00">September 17, 1939—9
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 18—7:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>206. Following from Biddle.</p>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“8, September 16, 6 p.m.</p>
                                <list>
                                    <label>1.</label>
                                    <item>Polish Government is leaving Poland by airplane via
                                        Rumania for a town in France not yet designated following
                                        precedent established by Belgian Government during World War
                                        and it is hoped and expected that all missions accredited to
                                        Polish Government will remain so accredited and will join it
                                        in the nearest future.</item>
                                    <label>2.</label>
                                    <item>I am now at Cernauti with entire staff since all missions
                                        were requested by Polish authorities to leave Kuty and
                                            Zaleszczyky.<note n="16" xml:id="d625fn16">Polish
                                            frontier town northeast of Kuty.</note></item>
                                    <label>3.</label>
                                    <item>Rumanian Government will today make <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> requesting missions accredited to Polish
                                        Government to leave Rumania as soon as possible. The Embassy
                                        is therefore leaving Cernauti for Bucharest where it will
                                        await Department’s instructions as to its further movements.
                                        In view of attitude of Rumanian Government I respectfully
                                        urge that such instructions be expedited. Biddle.”</item>
                                </list>
                            </quote>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>